      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Earnest money is a good-faith deposit you put down when making an offer on a house. It shows the seller you are serious about the purchase and helps secure the deal. It's held in an escrow account, which is a neutral third-party account, to keep the funds safe until all conditions of the sale are met. This ensures that if the deal falls apart for any reason, your money is protected.",
