      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the inspection reveals major issues, your contract likely has an inspection contingency, which allows you to renegotiate or back out of the deal. If you back out because of the damage and the contract allows it, you can usually get your earnest money back. However, if the seller refuses to budge and you proceed without addressing the issues, you risk forfeiting the earnest money according to the terms of your purchase agreement.",
